[4] California (Santa Clara county)
Date: Thu 3 May 2018
Source: LMT online [edited]
https://www.lmtonline.com/bayarea/article/6th-measles-case-confirmed-in-Santa-Clara-County-12883333.php


A 6th case of measles was confirmed in Santa Clara County, officials said, weeks after 5 people in the county and 2 others contracted the disease from exposure to a single infected person.

The most recent patient is unconnected to the earlier breakouts, officials said.

The latest incident involved a patient who had recently traveled internationally, Santa Clara County public health department spokeswoman Britt Ehrhardt said. Citing privacy laws, officials did not say whether the patient had been vaccinated.

The 1st case in the original outbreak was confirmed by county officials on [Wed 7 Mar 2018]. Four more were confirmed in Santa Clara County by [Thu 5 Apr 2018], officials said, in addition to another patient in Alameda County and a linked case in Nevada.

All of the original 7 patients were linked to a single unvaccinated traveler who had been exposed to the disease in Europe and returned to the Bay Area, officials said. The patients in the breakout were unvaccinated.

Officials said no public health preventative measures were required in response to the newest reported patient, but advised people to get vaccinated for measles if they had not been already.

Prior to this year's outbreak, measles was last reported in Santa Clara County in January 2017.

[Byline: Annie Ma]

