[5] California (Kern County): alert
Date: Sat 5 May 2018
Source: Bakersfield Now [edited]
http://bakersfieldnow.com/news/health/kern-health-officials-warn-of-measles-exposure-at-taco-bell


Health officials are warning that some Taco Bell customers could have been exposed to measles.

An infected person traveled though Kern County and stopped [Mon 30 Apr 2018] at the Taco Bell at California Avenue and Oak Street.

Kern County Public Health Services warned that anyone in the restaurant that day who wasn't vaccinated is at risk of developing measles. Public Health said symptoms from this incident could present themselves between [Tue 8 and Mon 21 May 2018]...

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention reports only 118 cases were recorded nationwide last year.

