[6] California (Fresno County): out of state travel - associated, alert
Date: Fri 4 May 2018 05:51 PM
Source: Fresno Bee [edited]
http://www.fresnobee.com/news/local/article210525324.html


Fresno County's Department of Public Health confirmed a case of measles in a Fresno County adult.

And the person may have exposed others during a visit to a local urgent care center, as well as the emergency room at Clovis Community Medical Center.

The infected individual traveled out of state, where the infection occurred, the department of public health announced Fri afternoon. After returning to California, the person developed the symptoms.

[See URL for locations and times infected individual may have exposed others to measles virus.]

Fresno County residents who were at [these] locations during those time frames and show any signs of measles should stay at home, verify their immunization status, and then contact their health care provider by telephone for instructions.

[Byline: Bryant-Jon Anteola]

