[8] New York ex European tourists
Date: Fri 4 May 2018 4:11 PM EDT
Source: NBC New York [edited]
<www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Jehovahs-Witness-Measles-Two-People-Exposed-New-York-481778841.html>


State health officials say 2 people in the greater New York City area have developed measles after they were exposed to 2 European tourists with measles at 3 Jehovah's Witness facilities last month [April 2018].

The 2 new cases of measles in Putnam County potentially put others at risk of developing measles, the state health department says. The risk is low, however, for people who have been vaccinated or are immune.

A 3rd person also developed measles from exposure to the tourists, but that person is a Connecticut resident and hasn't exposed it to anyone in New York, officials said. ...

[See URL for locations and times of possible exposure to infected individuals.]

This most recent incident marks the 4th month in a row that European tourists with confirmed cases of measles have traveled through the tri-state area. Officials previously warned of one incident in Manhattan and 2 at Newark Liberty International Airport.

